GCH 500: Foundations of Public Health. 3 credits.
Focuses on foundational principles and practices of public health, including historical origins, professional competencies, ethics, core functions and essential services, determinants of health, cultural competence, and communication strategies for diverse populations. Offered by Global and Community Health. May not be repeated for credit.
