GCH 515: Lesbian, Gay, Bisexual, Transgender, and Queer Health. 3 credits.
Examines health status and health disparities among lesbian, gay, bisexual, transgender, and queer (LGBTQ) communities across the lifespan. Measurement and methodological considerations in LGBTQ health research, as well as health-related interventions targeting LGBTQ populations will be emphasized. Notes: Offered every other year.  Upper level undergraduates interested in taking this course are encouraged to contact the instructor. Offered by Global and Community Health. May not be repeated for credit.
