GCH 700: Social and Ecological Determinants of Health. 3 credits.
Examines the evolution and transformation of public health in the United States and globally. Explores the social and ecological determinants of health that are associated with health disparities, and the public health methods that are essential for Public Health 3.0.  Analyzes the models, frameworks, methods, and policies that can be used to bridge the research-practice gap in public health. Offered by Global and Community Health. May not be repeated for credit.
