GCH 772: Social Epidemiology. 3 credits.
Focuses on applying epidemiological principles to the study of social factors and human health. Prepares students to measure population-level social determinants of health and quantitatively evaluate their relationship with health and disease. Requires students to translate information and analyses into summaries suitable for technical and non-technical audiences. Offered by Global and Community Health. May not be repeated for credit.
